archimate:BusinessObject.name: EIF Interoperability Level
archimate:BusinessObject.documentation:
DESCRIPTION: The New European Interoperability Framework (EIF) is a set of guidelines for developing public services. The EIF defines four interoperability levels, which cover legal, organisational, semantic and technical interoperability. Each level deserves special attention when a new European public service is established.
(1) European Commission, ISA Programme. The New European Interoperability Framework (EIF) for European public services. [Online] 2017. https://ec.europa.eu/isa2/eif_en.
